# Implementation Plan - Phase 7: Search & Rich Filtering

This plan details the design and changes to build a rich search and filtering system for courses, enabling students to search by text and filter by difficulty level, price range, language, and average rating.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **No Elasticsearch Dependency**: We use SQLite database-backed searching with `Q` queries for local development (which fallbacks to Django ORM full-text capabilities for production). This avoids the need to run an external Elasticsearch server locally.
> - **Search API Endpoint**: The search endpoint will be exposed at `/api/courses/search/` (accessible publicly without authentication) to support seamless searching from any part of the application.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [NEW] [filters.py](file:///c:/Users/shans/CascadeProjects/Online_Education_Platform/backend/courses/filters.py)
- Create `CourseFilter` class inheriting from `django_filters.FilterSet`:
  - `search`: Custom text filter performing a case-insensitive search across course `title`, `description`, and the mentor's `username`.
  - `level`: Exact match (`BEGINNER`, `INTERMEDIATE`, `ADVANCED`).
  - `language`: Case-insensitive contains match.
  - `min_price` and `max_price`: Numeric range filters on `price`.
  - `is_free`: Boolean filter which returns courses with `price = 0`.
  - `min_rating`: Custom filter that annotations average rating (`Avg('reviews__rating')`) and filters for courses with average rating greater than or equal to the query.
  - `ordering`: Orders by `price`, `-price`, `created_at`, `-created_at`, and `rating`.

#### [MODIFY] [views.py](file:///c:/Users/shans/CascadeProjects/Online_Education_Platform/backend/courses/views.py)
- Import `CourseFilter` from `.filters`.
- Create `CourseSearchView` inheriting from `rest_framework.generics.ListAPIView`:
  - Allow unauthenticated access using `permission_classes = [permissions.AllowAny]`.
  - Filter the query set to only return approved and published courses: `Course.objects.filter(is_approved=True, is_published=True)`.
  - Annotate results with `avg_rating` (`Avg('reviews__rating')`) and `enrollment_count` (`Count('enrollments')`).
  - Use `CourseFilter` as the filterset class.
  - Customize the list response to include `facets` alongside the results (min/max price, available levels, available languages) to help the frontend build dynamic filters.

#### [MODIFY] [serializers.py](file:///c:/Users/shans/CascadeProjects/Online_Education_Platform/backend/courses/serializers.py)
- Implement `CourseSearchSerializer` inheriting from `CourseListSerializer` to include `avg_rating` and `enrollment_count`.

#### [MODIFY] [urls.py](file:///c:/Users/shans/CascadeProjects/Online_Education_Platform/backend/courses/urls.py)
- Route the `CourseSearchView` at `path('courses/search/', CourseSearchView.as_view(), name='course-search')` (preceding the ViewSet routes).

